<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00124</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTION 10 OF REPUBLIC ACT 7832 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS AN ACT PENALIZING THE PILFERAGE OF AND THEFT OF POWER TRANSMISSION LINES/MATERIALS, RATIONALIZING SYSTEM LOSSES BY PHASING OUT PILFERAGE A COMPONENT THEREOF, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides that “ THE COSTS OF SYSTEM LOSSES SHALL NOT BE CHARGEABLE OR PASSED ON TO THE CONSUMERS AND SHALL  BE FOR THE ACCOUNT OF THE PRIVATE ELECTRIC UTILITIES AND/OR RURAL ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>FERNANDEZ, DAN S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2019-08-14)</td><td>2. Salceda (000 2019-08-15)</td><tr><td>3. Tambunting (000 2019-08-20)</td><td>4. Sy-Alvarado (000 2019-08-27)</td><tr><td>5. Marquez (000 2019-08-29)</td><td>6. Roman (000 2019-11-04)</td><tr><td>7. Malapitan (000 2019-11-28)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ENERGY ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>